  "texts": [
    "To overcome this difficulty, the second scheme resolves an additional hyperbolic equation for the parallel component of the heat flux (Rempel, 2017; Warnecke and Bingert, 2020), which is the problematic one in the case of astrophysical plasma.",
    "This allows the use of larger values of the time step and reduces the cost of the simulations.",
    "To do this, we rewrite the heat flux",
    "and introduce a hyperbolic equation for its evolution,",
    "Here, τ is the relaxation time usually set proportional to the computational time step (see Section 3.1.1)."
  ]
}